TY  - JOUR
AU  - Paravisini, Daniel
AU  - Rappoport, Veronica
AU  - Schnabl, Philipp
AU  - Wolfenzon, Daniel
T1  - Dissecting the Effect of Credit Supply on Trade: Evidence from Matched Credit-Export Data
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdu028
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 82
IS  - 1
SP  - 333
EP  - 359
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We estimate the elasticity of exports to credit using matched customs and firm-level bank credit data from Peru. To account for non-credit determinants of exports, we compare changes in exports of the same product and to the same destination by firms borrowing from banks differentially affected by capital-flow reversals during the 2008 financial crisis. We find that credit shocks affect the intensive margin of exports, but have no significant impact on entry or exit of firms to new product and destination markets. Our results suggest that credit shortages reduce exports through raising the variable cost of production, rather than the cost of financing sunk entry investments.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdu028
ER  - 



